The U.S. EPA Risk Management Regulation identifies three levels of requirements for industrial processes.  Program 1 can be applied to any process which has not had a "significant" release of a regulated substance over the five year period prior to the RMPlan submittal date and for which the worst-case release does not affect "public receptors" (e.g., residences, parks and recreation areas, commercial/industrial facilities, hospitals).  Given that the TDI process contains substantial quantities of that if released outdoors could affect public receptors, it does not qualify for Program 1.  Program 2 applies to this facility because it is not subject to OSHA's Process Safety Management (PSM) program.  

